==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κυβερνητικός]]''' (''kybernetikos'') "good at steering, good pilot", (''kybernetike techne'': "the pilot's art", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κυβερνισμός]]''', '''[[κυβέρνησις]]''' (''kybernismos'', ''kybernesis'') "steering, pilotage, guiding", from '''[[κυβερνάω]]''' (''kybernao'') "to steer, to drive, to guide, to act as a pilot".

===Adjective===
'''cybernetic'''
# an art/study of or related to governing, controlling processes and communication.
# related to [[computer]]s and [[internet]]

